          <valueString value="Ms. Torres presented with 12-hour history of migratory right iliac fossa pain, fever 38.2°C, and elevated inflammatory markers. CT abdomen confirmed acute uncomplicated appendicitis; emergency laparoscopic appendectomy performed. Specimen showed acute phlegmonous appendicitis on histology; no perforation. Discharged day 1 post-op, tolerating diet; wound check and GP follow-up in 1 week." />
